    <text id="F8020T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Chambers sends Cameron a manuscript and comments upon the Dred Scot decision.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
              

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1859-06-29"><abbr expan="June">Jun</abbr> 29 59</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I send you with pleasure <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> copy of my Tribute to the Irish
                    &amp; Scotish Early Settlers of <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Penns</abbr> as I
                    learn you have some partiality for the Record. My motions are disclosed in the
                    Preface. Could I have <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> on the <hi rend="underline">life</hi>
                    extended to me, I would have extended this work. I felt however, as my Time of
                    Life is matter of Grace; that my <unclear>thrusion</unclear> &amp;
                        <unclear>term</unclear> are past, &amp; I must not be surprised with a
                    Summons to quit, at the Word of my Heavenly Master-</p>
                <p>You will accept my thanks for the copy of the <orig reg="Judge's">Judge</orig>
                    opinions in the Dred Scott case. I cannot concurr with the majority
                    <unclear>of</unclear> the Court in that notable Case-</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">George Chambers</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">The <abbr expan="Honorable">Hon.</abbr> Simon
                        Cameron</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
